      "content": "It's natural to feel lost and confused right now, but it's also important to remember that you are not alone in your feelings. You are not stuck in this mess forever. There is still hope for a better future, even if it's hard to see right now. Sometimes, separation can be a painful but necessary part of growth and healing. You don't have to be together to be happy or fulfilled. You can find your own path and create your own happiness. It's okay to grieve the loss of your relationship, but it's also okay to move forward and find new meaning in your life. You deserve to find your own light, even if it's different from the light you shared with your partner. Remember, you are still here, still alive, and still capable of finding joy and fulfillment. Don't give up hope, even when it feels like everything is falling apart. You have the strength to overcome this, and you don't have to face it alone. There are people who care about you and want to help you find your way. It's okay to ask for help, and it's okay to take a break from the darkness. You deserve to find your own light.",
